name: ORIGINAL "How I've Missed Your Laugh Boy"
description:
Jasmine Star
Acrylic Painting on Canvas
"How I've Missed Your Laugh Boy"
12in. x 16in. with 1.5in. Depth
2013

This is the Original Painting.  This Hawaiian seascape is painted black around the sides of the canvas.. it is coated with a UV protective glaze and ready to hang with staples on the back.

~

Yes.. different and lighter than the majority of my work; I much enjoyed painting this peaceful Piece!  It is from a photo taken by a women who came into my gallery (just returning to Portland OR. from Hawaii).  After viewing one of my newer pieces "That's What I Was Thinking" she was taken aback by the similarity between this piece and the dark blue seascape she had captured.  I admit, it was oddly similar, having never been there.  She then shared with me other photos of her stay in Hawaii, "How I've Missed Your Laugh" being one of them!

About the title:
At the finish, the combination of colours and form looked to me of the sound of an old friends laughter; an honest, lighthearted, crackling rasp that always made me smile :)
